author: Dana Scott
title: You'll Be Watching This Unbelievable Ending of Today's Michigan/Michigan State Game for Years to Come
text:
After 89 years of playing each other, all Michigan and Michigan State fans will remember how crazy today's game ended. The Wolverines were shocked on the last play of today's game against their interstate rival. After trailing 23-21 in the fourth quarter, Michigan had the ball and was ready to punt and milk the clock. Instead, the unthinkable happened. The snap was fumbled by the kicker, and the Spartans recovered it quickly, then running it in for the game-winning touchdown. Final score 27-23.
